Comment.value:
ABORTING: If the dialogue is escaped from or aborted and the local set on Ayala "Main_Plot_Told" is not set to 1, it should set to 1. 

Note also that there are a number of places in the initial conversation where some actions will need to be performed in the midst of dialogue... these are all mentioned in Comments already. All of Drogan's dialogue is marked with "No Animation" so he can remain lying down during it. Whenever Ayala is mentioned as doing something else (like doing a GET_LOW animation to 'treat' Drogan) her dialogue is also marked with "No Animation" so she can continue doing it and talk at the same time.

Ayala's main dialogue is meant to be used up and until the point where a PC carrying the tower statue enters Drogan's Home. When that occurs, the module local "Drogan_Healed" should be set to 2, Drogan should stop playing his laying-down animation and Drogan should initiate dialogue with whoever holds the tower statue. That will be, in effect, the end of the chapter... this is why Ayala has no dialogue (she should not be able to be spoken to once Drogan starts). If this changes, Ayala will need some ending dialogue.
